				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Should I retire bard until my broken arm heals? <a name="51516"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 12 04 6:29 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>My bard just hit 24th recently.  I was in a car accident a week ago and broke left arm and rib on my right side.  Twistin and kiting took both hands, so I'm not sure if I should shelve her until cast comes off in 8 to 12 weeks.  I've been playing my necro in the meantime as she is slower paced. but prefer my bard as she definitely more fun.  This is my first bard and this site has been my bible on learning the ropes. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
Any ideas or suggestions?</span></td>
