				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Should I retire bard until my broken arm heals? <a name="51521"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 12 04 6:52 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I hate to here that...get well soon!
<br />

<br />
As far as your question, disabilities ( affecting twisting) have come up a couple of times over the years.
<br />

<br />
You can get a Nostromo n52 and use it to auto twist for you (mixed results, most people do not think this is ideal) or you can use macros for kiting (doable but awkward). However, I don't think you can effectively do groups with one of those solutions, unless you have an understanding group. Heck, I see bards at 24 who don't appear to twist at all.
<br />

<br />
No answer other than I personally would shelve the bard for that time.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
